The paper deals with recommendation systems, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on ranking loss functions and session-based recommendations could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the use of natural language processing techniques to model user behavior could make it relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper's focus on improving performance over classical collaborative filtering approaches could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the recommendations are related to visual content.
